 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This traditional Welsh tea bread, which translates literally as ‘speckled bread’, has several variations. It can be made with yeast, but this is a quicker version without. The tea-soaked fruits give the loaf a lovely sticky texture and it keeps well, too. Best enjoyed cut in thick slices and spread with butter."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","10h","12 slices"]}